# Local auto-push (current branch)

Opt-in per repo, `MODE: Local` only. When active, the agent commits and pushes at end of any reply that modified project files.

## Trigger gate

Active only when all true: (1) `MODE: Local`; (2) `.cursor/.local-auto-push` exists at repo root; (3) this reply (incl. any returned sub-agent reply) modified at least one project file — i.e. any path outside `.cursor/agent-transcripts/**`, `terminals/**`, the marker itself, and gitignored paths.

If only excluded paths changed → `Auto-push: N/A (no project-file modifications)`. If any of (1)–(3) fails → name the failing condition in the Done check and skip.

To enable in a project: see `templates/local-auto-push-marker.md`.

## Preconditions (any failure → stop, do **not** push)

1. Not on detached HEAD (`git symbolic-ref --quiet HEAD`).
2. Pre-push hygiene clean per `docs-sync-before-finish.mdc` (docs, `.gitignore`, secret-leak, change-impact grep sweep).
3. `CHANGELOG.md` entry + version bump per `versioning-and-changelog.mdc`.
4. No merge/rebase/cherry-pick/bisect in progress (no `.git/MERGE_HEAD`, `REBASE_HEAD`, `CHERRY_PICK_HEAD`, `BISECT_LOG`).
5. Fast-forward possible: `git fetch origin "$(git rev-parse --abbrev-ref HEAD)"`; if remote ahead, `git pull --rebase`; any conflict → `git rebase --abort` and stop. Never auto-resolve.

## Push procedure — MUST

1. `git add -A`
2. `git commit -m "<type>(<scope>): <subject>" -m "<body>"` (Conventional Commits per `versioning-and-changelog.mdc`).
3. Push current branch: first push `git push -u origin HEAD`, subsequent `git push origin HEAD`.
4. Watch CI to a documented end state per `post-push-ci-green.mdc`.

## You MUST NOT

- `git push --force` / `--force-with-lease`. Ever. Push rejected → stop.
- Push any branch other than the current one.
- Stage a file that triggered the secret-leak hard stop.
- Bypass the version bump.
- Push on detached HEAD, mid-merge/rebase, or after a non-fast-forward you couldn't cleanly resolve.
- Push from a Scenario B sub-agent (see `00-universal-core.mdc`).

## Required report

- `Auto-push: <pushed | N/A: <reason> | blocked: <reason>>`
- If pushed: branch, commit SHA, version `X.Y.Z` → `X.Y.Z'`.
- If blocked: name the failing precondition.
